      <p>Why not "Keys Per Second" or "Lines Per Hour"? WPM has endured for over a century (dating back to the typewriter era) because of its human scale. We speak at roughly 130–150 WPM. We read at roughly 200–250 WPM. Having a typing metric that sits in the 40–100 range makes it easy for us to visualize how close we are to "real-time" communication. When you hit 120 WPM on <a href="https://typer.uz">Typer.uz</a>, you are literally typing at the speed of human speech!</p>

